pet_description: Beautiful, independent, outdoor adult cat.  Owner had a stroke and can no longer care for his cats. We are trying to assist in finding Annabelle and three other cats a home.  Has been spayed and is current on shots.  She is a little shy at first but once she gets to know you she is loving and curious.   Please call us for further details.

Oliver is a sweet 2 year old male St. Bernard who needs a new, loving forever home.  Unfortunately, his family had some troubles and have to go back to Ohio and cannot keep him.

Oliver has lived with children (ages 6 and 8).  He is a loving, sweet boy who loves belly rubs! He knows basic commands and is pretty good on a leash. 

Neutered, shots, microchip - $200 Adoption fee

Charlie is an adorable two year old female St. Bernard whose family has to move and cannot take her with them  She is a good girl who has lived with other dogs, 

If you are interested in adopting Charlie, please submit an online application at www.sincitysaintrescue.org

Spayed, shots, microchip $200 adoption fee.

Valentina came to us on December 20th with a tummy full of puppies - so full she gave birth that same day! She is a friendly girl, approximately 3 years old and 40 lbs. She knows some basic commands - and has a sassy personality as you can see from her sticking out the tongue photo! If you are interested in adopting please submit an application at www.waggingtailsrescue.org.

Meet me Saturday from 11 to 1 at Petco, 645 S. Green Valley Pkwy in Henderson.  If you are interested in adopting please submit an application at www.waggingtailsrescue.org.  Shasta came to us a couple of months ago, one of 160 dogs taken out of a hoarding situation. This sweet girl is very shy but we proud of her progress! She loves to go for walks and plays well with other dogs. She is not at all aggressive but is hesitant to let people touch her so she will need a home where they are comfortable letting her come to them at her own pace. Shasta is approximately 2 years old and 12 lbs.

Mesa is a 1 year old girl who weighs in at a whopping 4 1/2 lbs! This sweet girl loves people and does well with other dogs. She was born with a head tilt but it doesn’t stop her from living a life full of playtime and love. Mesa is spayed, microchipped and current on vaccines, her adoption fee is $250.

If you are interested in adopting please submit an application at www.waggingtailsrescue.org.

Jesse is a 1 year old cutie who would love a family to call his own. He is a shy boy at first meeting but warms up quickly and loves attention. He does well with other dogs too! Jesse weighs 10 lbs. He is neutered, microchipped and current on vaccines, his adoption fee is $250. 

If you are interested in adopting please submit an application at www.waggingtailsrescue.org.

Jackson is a 1 year old handsome boy who loves to play and be active! He has been raised with kids and a small dog so he is very tolerant. Jack is house trained and crate trained too. He is still very puppy like and will chew on things when he gets bored so lots of toys are a must. He weighs approximately 75 lbs. He is neutered, microchipped and current on vaccines, his adoption fee is $250.

If you are interested in adopting please submit an application at www.waggingtailsrescue.org.

We received a call from the shelter who knows we have a weakness for Boxers - this handsome boy's time was up and he needed a place to go urgently. One look at his smooshed, slightly crooked face and we couldn't say no. Jughead is an 84 lb, 10 year old Boxer who is as easy as they come. He gets along with dogs of all sizes and is fine with cats too. He is friendly with people and enjoys getting his back scratched. Jug is neutered, microchipped and current on vaccines, his adoption fee is $100.

 If you are interested in adopting please submit an application at www.waggingtailsrescue.org.

Meet me Saturday from 11 to 1 at Petco, 645 S. Green Valley Pkwy in Henderson.

Mommy is a Jack Russel and Daddy is a mystery. We are expecting Lennon to be in the 20 lb range when fully grown. He is neutered, microchipped and current on vaccines, his adoption fee is $350.
If you are interested in adopting please submit an application at www.waggingtailsrescue.org.

Check out this cutie! Keno is a 10 year old, very sturdy boy, weighing in at about 40 pounds. He could definitely stand to shed a few pounds, so a healthy diet and appropriate exercise will be important for Keno. He is up to date on shots, microchipped, and neutered. Keno had a lump that was removed about one month ago on his right foot - tests have shown that it was benign/ non-cancerous. Keno is also dog door trained and has had no accidents in his foster home. 

Keno is a very obedient, good-natured, calm, and loving boy. He is a very curious and likes to follow you around to see what you are up to, especially when you are in the kitchen :) Keno is a big couch potato that likes to lay at your feet, and at times, likes to snuggle up to you on the couch as you watch TV. Keno enjoys the comforts of sleeping in bed with you at night. Keno is not a very active dog, but he does like to stroll around in the yard and enjoys rolling around in the grass. 

Ideal placement for Keno will be a single story home, no young children, and no cats. Keno gets along with other dogs that are non-dominant, not aggressive or non-territorial. If you have other dogs in the home it would be best if they are small to medium sized dogs.

If you are interested in adopting Keno and can meet his needs, please apply here http: www.snbtr.com/adoption/adoption-application to be considered. The adoption fee for Keno will be $200.

**Note – Keno and Kona are siblings from different litters, but had the same parents. Please see Kona’s photos and bio in the separate album. If you are interested in adopting the pair, please apply accordingly. To adopt Keno and Kona as the pair, the adoption fee will be $500.**

Poor Bubs. This devoted boy was found as a stray on the streets and turned into the shelter. We fell in love with him and decided to help him find his forever home. Bubs is a fun, friendly boy who adores all people that he meets. Bubs would do great in a home where he is the only pet. He is house trained and very well mannered (he sits, lays down, stays and shakes). Bubs is about 6 years old and is ready to become your new family member.

My name is Jesse and I'm an awesomely laid back chill guy.   A nice lady found me wandering in the desert and unfortunately my former family did not chip me so I am on the hunt for an adult only home who will make sure I'm an indoor only cat.   I'm not very needy, give me a window to perch in and some toys to play with and I'm a happy guy.  I am about 3 years old and am fully vetted (neutered/micro-chipped/shots).  I am happiest being your only furry family member. Someone with Siamese experience would be best as I am a typical Siamese.  There is an adoption fee and a safe home check required if you want to adopt me.

My name is Nacho! I'm a 2 year old Chihuahua mix and I weigh 7 lbs. I'm fine with other dogs, don't know about cats. I've met some kids at adoptions and they seemed to be ok. My foster parents say I'm a good, sweet boy and I'm doing better not crying when my foster mommy leaves for work. Oh, how I love to be with her. She makes sure I'm safe in the house before she leaves because I climb and jump to try and get her to stay home. If you become my new family, I will love to always be with you too. During the day I like to relax around the house with my foster dad. I'm getting better with my potty training and my favorite place is curled up under a blanket at the foot of the bed. I do get nervous when I go out in public and I do bark at dogs/people but I'm only trying to say hi. If you're looking for a new loyal friend, please come meet me at Petsmart on Eastern and Silverado Ranch (9869 Eastern Avenue). I'll be there Sat 11-4 & Sun 12-4, with all my buddies.

Pandora is an approximate 6 or 7 yr old beagle mix. We do not know with what. She is friendly and easy going. She was found on the streets and dumped in the shelter. Her life almost ended there as she was put on the list for being overweight. She definitely is overweight and we currently have her on a diet which we strongly encourage the adopter to continue and keep her at a healthy weight for her overall longevity and health. She does have endurance though and gets along with dogs and cats. She absolutely loves to play ball and fetch. She likes a good cuddle too. We recently had some cysts removed and did a dental on her teeth with 16 extractions. Now she is in perfect health and ready to go and have her own loving family and home.

Courtesy post:  Dudie is a large black, neutered male cat, about seven years old, UTD on shots and always been very healthy (never have had any issues with him for the six years I've had him).

Disco lost one of his back legs after being hit by a car but it doesn't hamper his mobility or spirit. He loves to walk around the adoption center on a leash. He runs, jumps and climbs as well as any 4 legged cat. He is muscular and strong. He is definately an alpha male who would do best as an only cat in the house.  He has a lot of personality and a mind of his own. He tends to gravitate toward men and would make a great pal. He is affectionate and can be very sweet. He has been through a lot of negatives and would love to settle down with a caring human buddy.  
~~Background~~~
Disco lost his original owner and BFF in a car accident.  He was very attached to this single young man.  It took a while for another young gentleman to come along interested in adopting him.  The gentleman visited Disco for months and they seemed to bond. The gentleman finally adopted him but he had 2 other cats, a male and a female. Disco didn't like the male and in short, terrorized him. The gentleman, eventually returned him to us. Disco took it really hard. He was unapproachable for a week.  Another couple of months went by when that gentleman brought a friend in to meet Disco.  His friend only had 1 cat , a female. He was hoping that Disco would get along with her but that didn't work either. So Disco is back with us hoping he can find a home of his own that he can share with a buddy without the interference of any other pets. He is an awesome cat that has been through a lot.  He would be a great cat for someone that wants companion

I am a happy go lucky petite 1 year old girl who loves to follow you around and have conversations with you. Rico is an energetic little mound of muscle who loves to run, can jump very high and has a lot of play stamina. He would love to be put to work and loves taking water breaks. He could use someone with bully breed experience, who is willing to exercise him physically and mentally. He could hike, run, play ball, etc.

Buddy is a very well trained boy looking for a family to love! He has been in training with a pack for the past year. He is now ready to be a great canine citizen with a family of his own. His trainer will offer a free session to whoever adopts him. He loves hiking and cuddling.

Raven is super friendly, has that pittie smile and tail wag that makes you love pitties the most. She is well behaved, though some leash training would always be helpful. She lives with two other dogs.. She is great with all people and loves attention, but isn't needy. She would love to hike, hang out at the lake or cuddle to Netflix. She is the quintessential family dog.

Duke is one of the most handsome, dogs you will ever meet! His gorgeous subtle, tiger brindle coloring is like nothing you've ever seen!   He is a low-maintenance, laid-back dude, that is great on a leash and loves to play fetch. Duke would love to meet you, so contact us today to meet the love of your life!

Ferdi is a young calm quiet boy looking for his person. He loves to love! We don’t know his history, but it is clear that he was not exposed too much of anything. Because he was so under socialized he is still learning to be with other dogs. He would be okay with some dogs, but he would prefer to be an only dog. He is great on leash and a lower energy dog. He is fully vaccinated, neutered, microchipped, and comes with 2 free training sessions as well as lifetime discounted boarding by Jennifer Gray at Sunny Day Acres.

Spartacus is 6 and can be in a home with other calm dogs.  He LOVES activity and in fact, helped his former mom train for a marathon.  He can also chill and is a love bug who loves to cuddle with his human. He helped his former mom through a very hard time, recovering from cancer.  The neighbors dogs and Spartacus didn't get along and the dogs were always barking through the fence.  One day Spartacus bit the dog and the neighbor reported him saying that she no longer felt safe.  Spartacus has since been in training and lives with a pack of dogs, doing very nicely with his manners.  His mom wants him back, but the stipulations for his return were too restrictive to him and she wants him to have the best life.  She asked us to rescue him from a high-kill shelter and find him his forever home.  He is a dog that bonds very strongly with his human.

Keats is a GREAT dog. He would be great at agility, because he is a NATURAL. He loves exercise, mental and physical and can also relax with his humans when the time comes. He is breathtakingly gorgeous and sweet. One of a kind and waiting for his lifetime love!!

Is the strong silent type more your speed? Chance is such a sweetheart that is looking for a home where he can LOVE on his people! Great on a leash and a good listener, he is eager to please, and would need an experience handler that could help him build his confidence. If you give him a CHANCE, you will not regret it!

Catori is so sweet and eager to please! When you meet her, you will fall in love with her happy smiling little chops and loving disposition. She would rather lean against you for lots of hugs and kisses than go for a walk. The Samadhi Legacy Foundation believes she should be given the tools of training to set her up for success. Catori needs the perfect home with a responsible owner, to protect her, love and train her. (Good with large dogs, just not small dogs or small animals.)

Sweet little Flower is looking for a home of her own, and a family for her to love. She enjoys long walks where she can sniff everything out and explore! Friendly Flower LOVES people, likes other dogs, and always has a "Happy Tail"!

This sweet and goofy boy is as loyal as they come! This combined with his alertness makes him a great guard dog…you won’t miss ANYTHING that goes on with him around! Curious Ollie loves car rides and going on lots of adventures!

Roo is a diamond in the rough! As the story we were told goes, this sweet girl had been through quite a bit of training before her previous family surrendered her to the shelter - including snake avoidance training! They loved her a lot but she simply had too much energy for them to handle. She really is a good girl, and look at those ears! She's friendly and quiet and is currently working with a trainer to really assess her personality and work through any rough edges she has. She rides like a dream in the car, walks well on leash, knows all her basic obedience, and is just a friendly happy-go-lucky dog who would make any family very lucky to share a life with her.

Roo is around 3 years old, around 50lbs, spayed, microchipped, and is up-to-date on vaccines and deworming. She gets along with dogs with proper introductions.

Penelope has officially been dubbed "too smart for her own good!" She was picked up as a stray and has clearly had several litters, but we don't know much more than that about her history. What we do know is that while working with trainers she doesn't need a ton of guidance, she picks up on stuff immediately, and then turns it into a game. Smart dogs are so much fun! She has already learned her basics and is now working on sit- and down-stays which really works on her patience and focus. She would love an active family who take the time to regularly work on mental exercises to keep her brain moving and in tip-top shape. Keeping up with her is a blast and she's going to make her new family so happy. Penelope loves people and as one of our newer pups is still learning manners and how to control her excitement, but she's already come a long way and we know she's destined for great things.

Penelope is around 4 years old, around 60 lbs, spayed, microchipped, and is up-to-date on vaccines and deworming.

Tonka is a comedian. He is the goofiest and everybody who meets him falls in love. He's built like a little truck and he's deceptively heavy and strong, but he only uses his powers for good. He loves his walks and playtime, and also loves getting back into the air conditioning and doing a full sploot on the cool tile with his little sausage legs sticking straight out. Tonka came to us with pretty severe cherry-eye which was corrected by a veterinary ophthalmologist and now he is good to go! He's seriously the best and we're shocked we've even had him the few months we have.

Tonka is around 3 years old, 70lbs, neutered, microchipped, and is up-to-date on vaccines and deworming. He gets along with dogs with proper introductions.

We love Leo! Leo was adopted from our rescue as a puppy and was re-surrendered after about three years due to some major changes in the family. He did nothing wrong and in fact, they did an amazing job shaping him into a well mannered, extremely well behaved, fit healthy boy. Leo is well trained, listens amazingly well, is great in the car, and is all around a great dog. He's a little shy at first but quickly warms up and then is the goofiest guy who loves cuddles and to play. 

Leo is around 3 years old, 70bs, neutered, microchipped, and is up-to-date on vaccines and deworming. He loves other dogs and kids. He can be adopted with or without Lulu, but without her, he would do best with other friendly playful dog(s) in the home.

Nico loves cuddles! No really, he loves to give kisses. He's such a little cutie, and he's so happy to just lay around and people watch with you. Nico is one of our newer pups and we're still working on getting to know him completely, but he's definitely a lover. He's great on walks and likes to lounge in the sun and get love and attention. He's great in the car and has never met a stranger. He's currently working with our trainers to learn and sharpen his manners and obedience and he's going to be a fantastic dog for the right family!

Nico is around 4 years old, 55 lbs, neutered, microchipped, and is up-to-date on vaccines and deworming.

Sophie was a stray found eating from a pile of trash. All of her remaining 11 teeth were rotten and infected – causing significant pain – and had to be removed. Sophie will need to be on soft food for the remainder of her years. But despite her abandonment, she is the sweetest, friendliest Doberlady you could hope to meet. She loves to lean against you and would be happiest if she could be your queen bee couch potato with no cats. Sophie was found with a 10-week-old puppy, Sunny, who we believe is her puppy. Adorable Sunny, listed separately, with her one brown and one blue eye and different coat, is clearly not a pure Doberman, but she has inherited the Doberman Velcro trait. To adopt Sophie and/or Sunny, please go to www.drnv.org and complete an application.

Sunny, with one blue eye and one brown eye and a different coat, is a 6-month-old Doberman mix who was a stray that DRNV took in with her mom, Sophie, a purebred 5-year-old Doberman. Sunny has inherited the Doberman Velcro trait. She isn’t fond of cats but loves her mom. Both were found eating from a pile of trash. Mom Sophie’s teeth were so rotten and infected that the 11 she had remaining had to be removed. She will have to be on soft food for the remainder of her years. But despite their abandonment, both Sunny and Sophie are very sweet, friendly and loving. To adopt Sunny and/or Sophie, please go to www.drnv.org and complete an application.

Peanut is a 6 1/2-year-old black and tan Doberman whose mom fell on hard times and had to move and could not take him with her. He is a lovable big boy weighing just more than 100 pounds who may not always realize his size but is good with other dogs and kids. Peanut is a super smart love bug that would be content giving you kisses all day. To adopt Peanut, please go to www.drnv.org and complete an application.

Kobi is a 4-year-old Doberman whose owners needed to surrender him because he went after the chickens. And he wasn’t too keen about the cat, either. He gets along fine with big dogs and is very friendly and loving with people. He knows several commands and just needs the right family to call his forever home. To adopt Kobi, please go to www.drnv.org and complete an application.

Here is a very special case... small gray and white pot belly, sold as a MICRO MINI PIG, had eye issues as a piglet, and had two operations, is nearly blind today at 7 years old. Contact us today to schedule a visit to our pot bellied pig rescue and sanctuary. You will feel so good, we promise, thanks for looking! www.windys.org

Meet our favorite couple of the year.... Pebbles and Toby. Two pot bellied pigs, Pebbles was a "teacup" who outgrew her first home, and kept going after the dogs at her second home, so she made her way to Windy's this last summer. Toby was found by animal control running down the street in Vegas on Thanksgiving day, he was terrified and behaving feral, made his way to Windy's the next day. For Toby it was love at first sight! He is her shadow.... Pebbles tolerates him! They are pretty adorable together. The sleep beside my bed but love being outside all day.  Email us to meet these rescued babies. Home check before adoption and once during the first year.

A lady rescued Lil Larry from a couple who bought him as a piglet, and then got really sick and needed to find a place for him....

Questions? email me janice@windys.org
PLEASE PLEASE DO NOT BREED POT BELLIED PIGS!!!!

Hi, my name is BooBo. I'm about 3-4 years old now with a soft black coat and a little baby kitty voice. I  do talk when I'm trying to get your attention or looking for you. I'm pretty mellow, with occasional spurts of energy, but also play well independently. I get along well with other cats who are nice to me and don't mind if I go up to them to smell or rub against them.

I love to run and jump and climb...especially climb...but also to lounge or sleep in the cat trees or with you. I really enjoy outdoor views and sitting in the sunshine...watching the outdoor activities of the birds that come in the morning or a cat or two passing through. But I really love attention from my human, most of all.

I'm spayed, current on vaccinations, and micro-chipped.

Special Need: I have a mild anemia, so I eat Blue Buffalo Adult Indoor and supplement with wet food and do just fine. I just get my blood checked at my annual vet visits, meantime.

For more information, please call or text her foster mom, Shanna, at 702-205-1234.

CHELSEA is an incredibly sweet and special girl.  She apparently suffered a stroke during her spay surgery, before she came to us, and has made an amazing recovery with the love and devotion of her foster mom. She just has some exaggerated muscle responses, like stiffening and arching her back when pet, and walks a little like a tiny solider. She can now leap up on a chair or from one couch to the other and even climb the cat trees.

She's got the sweetest demeanor and an amazing spirit and LOVES to be brushed and pet, receive gentle kitty massages, and lye near her Human just relaxing, napping, watching TV or whatever you're doing. She's not comfortable being "held" for very long, but will sit or lye by you for long periods and is a wonderful little companion who will love you back.

Chelsea is spayed, micro-chipped and current on feline vaccinations.

***If you would like more information and/or feel you might be the purrfect pet parent(s) for Chelsea, please text or call 702-205-1234.

Gabby is going on aprrox 3 yrs old. She's still petite outgoing, loving, a young social butterfly and a total sweet-talker. She loves the company of other nice and non-aggressive/non-territorial cats who like her too and recently a little foster dog who is generally leery of some other cats getting too close. They now sit in the sun by the sliding glass door and clean each other. Yes...it's hilarious and beyond adorable!!!

She loves her cat trees and to jump up on the cat tree then to the high-up plant shelf. She interacts well with the other cats and would do best in a home with at least 1 of her current & familair pack-mates. She did not do well when separated from all for 2 previous meet & greets. She talks with a sweet meow...hence her name "Gabby".

Gabby becomes very nervous of change in a new environment, at least at first, so we've discovered that handling and reassuring her right away is very important to making sure she feels safe.

Gabby is spayed, current on feline vaccinations and micro-chipped.

If you would like more information about Gabby and  think your home could be her Forever Home, please call or text her foster mom at 702-205-1234.

pet_name: TINY - Special boy needs special home
pet_description:
Tiny is a friendly sociable male, approx 8 yrs old wih a curved over tail at the end from injury as a kitten.  He would do best in a peaceful loving home, with no other pets, where he will receive the time an attention he needs to thrive as an indoor-only cat.

He is neutered, current on feline vaccinations, and micro-chipped.

If you think you might be the answer to Tiny's prayers, please contact us for more information. Thank you.

AUBREY is approximately (up to)  1 yr old, according to the vet. Found undernourished and frightened. She has now become a loving, affectionate sweetheart who would make a wonderful companion to someone who wants an active, vocal, fur-baby who just wants to love and be loved.

She's petite and full of life, eats well and has put on the healthy weight she needed. She loves attention and will sit on the bathroom counter and watch her foster mom get ready for the day and talk to her as if conversing. She will follow you around, give head-butts, and wants to sleep with you.

Aubrey may be compatible with another mellow kitty who is not threatening and non-reactive as Aubrey gets to know them. She is   doing amazing and would also do well as a pampered & adored only-pet in a peaceful, loving home with lots of attention and kitty comforts.

She loves being pet and gently brushed with a soft-bristle brush.

Aubrey is litter-box trained, uses a scratching post, spayed, current on feline vax and will be micro-chipped prior to re-homing.

If you think you could possibly be Aubrey's forever angel, please call or text her foster mom at 702-205-1234 for more information.

Meet Major, at 12 year young and only 8 lbs Major is a laid back, loving Chihuahua. He lives for snuggles, comfy dog beds, blankets and being near his person. All this lil guy wants to do is show you how sweet and loving he is. Major ask for so little but gives a ton of love in return. He is charming and sensitive but you can tell he's overcome so much. He needs time to know that you are not going be rough with him and once he feels safe he melts in your arms. Major is great on walks and great with non rambunctious kids or dogs.

He is missing a majority of his teeth so he would prefer a mixed meal of mostly soft food with a some hard food as well. Major is potty trained with the understanding that this lil guy requires a couple of extra bathroom most likely due to being a senior.
If you are looking for a quiet, gentle soul that will give you unconditional love, look no further. Mr. Major has it all. ?? call diana 702-239-7986

My name is Lucy! I was rescued by my foster mom after I unfortunately was hit by a car and taken to the shelter. My old owners didn’t want to reclaim me so the nice people at A Home 4 Spot stepped in and took me to the vet right away.  I broke both my back legs pretty badly and shattered lower pelvis so I needed surgery ASAP. Thankfully I’m recovering well and will be ready for adoption soon! I’m a very sweet 7 year old chihuahua mix (I might have some corgi in me but I’m not quiet sure). I’m a tiny little girl and only weight about 6lbs. I am very grateful to be able to walk again even though I’m a little slower. I need a stable surface and some patience but my tail never stops wagging and I’m very happy to follow you around. I get along with most small dogs but would prefer a mellow quiet household since I need to be careful with my legs. I’m spayed, microchipped, up to date on vaccines, and house trained. If you want to give me a loving forever home please text my foster mom at 406.260.1813. There is an adoption fee.

They are up-to-date on vaccines, spayed, and microchipped. This tiny little girl is Linda. She is 1 yr old 9 lb Chihuahua mix. We got Linda from our local shelter a few days ago.  Her owners surrendered her with two 6 month old puppies and she had recently given birth.   Linda is only a year old herself.  She spent the first few days crying and pacing.  It was utterly heart wrenching.   She would lean herself into me and rub herself on me for attention.  As she started to open up, I started learning how amazing this little chi is. Her temperament is sweet and she loves to be in your personal space and being cuddled by her humans. She’s done great with big and small dogs, but really seems to want to stick with her person more than anything else.    So far she has been doing great with potty training and she is very well behaved.  If you want a dog that will follow you everywhere and be your best friend, Linda is it.
